# Notion Sync Checkpoint

## Principle

Notion is the source of truth. Code without Notion entries is undocumented. Documentation without code is a lie.

## Session End Checklist (MANDATORY)

Before ending any work session, verify:

### 1. Workers Registry (`collection://cc6b66a2-1904-4c7a-a25f-916146282089`)
- [ ] Every new parser → entry with Type, Status, Countries, Approach, Notes
- [ ] Every new worker → entry with Type (Enricher/Cleaner/Verifier), Status, Notes
- [ ] Status updated for any modified parser/worker

### 2. Knowledge Base (`collection://c973a8be-f1be-462c-bf14-55c47f0c5708`)
- [ ] Every completed task → Status: Done + Completed Date
- [ ] Every new decision → Type: Decision with Category, Context, Alternatives, Impact
- [ ] Every discovered bug/task → Status: Backlog with full Notes
- [ ] Every blocked item → Status: Blocked with Blocker description

### 3. Current State Page (`3182ac10-63c8-811c-8cfe-fd40919d8e20`)
Update if ANY of these changed during session:
- Version numbers or release status
- Parser/entity/worker counts
- Tech stack (deps, router, fonts)
- Active blockers
- Infrastructure changes

### 4. CLAUDE.md
Update if ANY of these changed:
- Tech stack versions (check package.json)
- Router type (check App.tsx)
- Font family (check app.css)
- Current mode / priorities
- Team/role changes

## Documentation Gap Recovery

If you discover undocumented parsers, workers, or decisions at any point:
1. STOP current work
2. Backfill all missing Notion entries
3. Resume only after gaps are filled

## Anti-patterns from history

- Building 3 workers without logging any of them
- Current State page 8+ days stale
- CLAUDE.md claiming Vite 6 when package.json has Vite 7
- MEMORY.md never created despite being in the protocol
